The paper deals with object recognition systems and the exploration of learning procedures for sparse convolutional networks. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of unsupervised pre-training and supervised fine-tuning, which are common techniques in machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also introduces a new single phase supervised learning procedure, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the recognition rate on datasets, which suggests that it could also belong to the natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-category.
